The lemma `injective_zHat` asserts the injectivity of the map $j_2: \mathcal{O}^\wedge \to D^\wedge$. The map $j_2$ is defined as the composition of the inclusion $\mathcal{O}^\wedge \to \mathbb{Q} \otimes_{\mathbb{Z}} \mathcal{O}^\wedge$ (which is `Algebra.TensorProduct.includeRight`) and an isomorphism of algebras.

Since algebra isomorphisms are bijective (and thus injective), it suffices to show that `includeRight` is injective. The injectivity of the base change $M \to \mathbb{Q} \otimes_{\mathbb{Z}} M$ (which corresponds to `includeRight`) holds if $M$ is a flat $\mathbb{Z}$-module and the map $\mathbb{Z} \to \mathbb{Q}$ is injective.
Here, $\mathcal{O}^\wedge = \mathcal{O} \otimes_{\mathbb{Z}} \hat{\mathbb{Z}}$. Since $\mathcal{O}$ is a free $\mathbb{Z}$-module (Hurwitz quaternions) and $\hat{\mathbb{Z}}$ is a flat $\mathbb{Z}$-module (profinite integers), their tensor product $\mathcal{O}^\wedge$ is flat over $\mathbb{Z}$.
The map $\mathbb{Z} \to \mathbb{Q}$ is the canonical inclusion, which is injective (`Int.cast_injective`).
We use `TensorProduct.includeRight_injective` which encapsulates this flatness argument.

```lean
namespace HurwitzRatHat

/-- The "profinite Hurwitz quaternions" over the finite adeles of ‚Ąö; a free rank 4 module
generated by 1, i, j, and (1+i+j+k)/2. -/
scoped notation "D^" => HurwitzRatHat

noncomputable instance : Ring D^ := Algebra.TensorProduct.instRing

/-- The inclusion from D=‚Ąö+‚Ąöi+‚Ąöj+‚Ąök to D ‚äó ūĚĒł, with ūĚĒł the finite adeles of ‚Ąö. -/
noncomputable abbrev j‚āĀ : D ‚Üí‚āź[‚Ą§] D^ := Algebra.TensorProduct.includeLeft
-- (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ą§ ‚Ąö ūĚďě ZHat).symm.trans Algebra.TensorProduct.includeLeft

